%% xstream streaming - Scenario 1: Initial Playback (happy path)
%% Covers click-play through first pixels. One of four scenario diagrams.
%% Regenerate .drawio via: open_drawio_mermaid with the contents of this file.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant VP as VideoPlayer
    participant PC as PlaybackController
    participant SS as StreamingService
    participant BM as BufferManager
    participant GQL as GraphQL
    participant CH as chunker
    participant FF as ffmpeg
    participant ST as StreamRoute

    U->>VP: click play
    VP->>PC: startPlayback(res)
    Note right of PC: open span playback.session
    PC->>BM: init(mimeType)
    BM-->>PC: sourceopen, SourceBuffer ready
    PC->>GQL: startTranscode(videoId, res, 0, 300)
    GQL->>CH: startTranscodeJob
    Note right of CH: jobId = SHA-1(fp + res + range)
    CH->>FF: spawn ffmpeg
    Note right of CH: open transcode.job span
    CH-->>GQL: ActiveJob running
    GQL-->>PC: rawJobId, globalJobId
    PC->>SS: start(jobId, 0, onSegment, ctx)
    Note right of SS: open chunk.stream span
    SS->>ST: GET /stream/jobId + traceparent
    Note right of ST: open stream.request span
    FF->>CH: init.mp4 written
    CH->>ST: notifySubscribers
    ST-->>SS: framed init.mp4
    SS->>BM: onSegment(init, first=true)
    BM->>BM: appendBuffer(init)
    FF->>CH: segment_0000.m4s written
    CH->>ST: notifySubscribers
    ST-->>SS: framed segment
    SS->>BM: onSegment(data)
    BM->>BM: appendSegment, drainQueue
    BM-->>PC: afterAppendCb fires
    Note right of PC: bufferedEnd reached startup target
    PC->>BM: video.play
    Note over BM: status playing, pixels on screen

    Note over SS,ST: Binary framing per frame - 4-byte BE uint32 length plus N bytes fMP4. First frame always init.mp4 (moov). Rest are .m4s (moof plus mdat).
